================
description
================

1) This program accept two directory names from user and move all files from source 
	directory to destination directory.
2) Required directory names will be taken from command line

================
about the code
================

	input	:	directory_Name1(source), directory_Name2(destination)
	output	:	result - Status of execution
 			
=============
How to run
=============

	make	:	compile the code and generates executable file as "myexe"
	make run:	run the executable with command line argument
			for this you have to pass parameter as: 
			
			$ make run p1="parameter_value1" p2="parameter_value2"
	
=============
NOTE
=============

	1)If the given directory_file is unable to open, it will display the appropriate reason.
	2)This program implements "$ mv" command
		
